funds and non-residents, FX hedging demand from merchandise trade remains a significant part of the market. This paper utilizes a transactional database that disaggregates exporters according to their firm-level characteristics in order to explain their hedging behavior over periods of exchange rate fluctuation. FX hedging by exporters is found to be sensitive to the movement in exchange rate and past hedging experience. These sensitivities give rise to periods of panic or complacency. The effects also vary across exporters with different sizes.\"));\n}\n;\nMDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;","fields":{"slug":"/dp/081/fx-hedging-behavior-among-thai-exporters-a-micro-level-evidence/","collection":"dp","shorturl":"/dp/081/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"FX Hedging Behavior among Thai Exporters: A Micro-level Evidence","subtitle":null,"series":null,"authors":["Thethach Chuaprapaisilp","Nathapong Rujiravanich","Bovornrach Saengsith"],"date":"2018-02-12T00:00:00.000Z","updated":null,"cover":null,"excerpt":null,"bibliography":null,"topics":null,"tags":null,"layout":null,"pdf":{"publicURL":"/static/ead86d8a590bed5b4e843fc03b833a71/pier_dp_081.pdf"}},"authors":[{"frontmatter":{"memberid":"Bovornrach Saengsith","title":"Bovornrach Saengsith","org":"bot","email":"BovornrS@bot.or.th","image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/dd515/profile.jpg","srcSet":"/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/6ac16/profile.jpg 50w,\n/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/e07e1/profile.jpg 100w,\n/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/dd515/profile.jpg 200w,\n/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/47930/profile.jpg 400w","sizes":"(min-width: 200px) 200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/dbc4a/profile.webp 50w,\n/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/d8057/profile.webp 100w,\n/static/84caa5c3c8d5ac32c19f466d89e55906/2e34e/profile.